## Introduction
This project was completed as part of the Digital Literacy course. The aim of this project is to develop essential digital skills required in today’s digital world. It focuses on creating a professional online presence, using digital tools effectively, communicating properly through emails, and understanding cyber safety. This project helped me gain practical knowledge and improve my awareness about responsible digital behavior.

---

## Task 1: Infographic
For this task, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The infographic explains the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, and useful digital tools for students. I included points about strong passwords, safe browsing, and platforms like GitHub and LinkedIn. While designing the infographic, I found it interesting to organize information in a visually appealing format. The challenging part was selecting the right design and layout to present the information clearly.

---

## Task 2: Digital Portfolio
In this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub and LinkedIn. GitHub is used to store and manage coding projects, while LinkedIn is used for professional networking and career growth. I added my basic details such as education, branch, and year. These platforms will help me build my professional identity and showcase my skills over the next four years. I plan to regularly update my profiles with new projects and achievements.

---

## Task 3: Platforms
For this task, I used HackerRank to solve a beginner-level coding problem. This helped me understand basic problem-solving and coding logic. I also created a Google Form for a digital literacy awareness quiz. The form included multiple-choice and short-answer questions. These tools are useful for learning, practicing coding, and collaborating with others. They will help me improve my technical and academic skills.

---

## Task 4: Email Etiquette
In this task, I learned how to write professional emails. I created two emails: one requesting an assignment extension and another applying for an internship. I followed proper email structure including subject line, greeting, body, and closing. Poor digital communication can cause misunderstandings and create a negative impression. For example, using informal language or unclear messages in emails can lead to confusion. It is important to communicate clearly, politely, and professionally.

---

## Task 5: Cybercrime Awareness
In this task, I studied UPI fraud, which is a common cybercrime in India. I learned how attackers trick people into sharing sensitive information like OTPs and UPI PINs. I was surprised by how easily people can fall victim to such scams. As a result, I will be more careful and never share my personal or financial details online. I also learned how to report cybercrime using the official portal and helpline.

---

## Conclusion
This project helped me understand the importance of digital literacy. I learned how to use digital platforms, communicate professionally, and stay safe online. These skills are very important for students in today’s digital age. Overall, this project improved my awareness and confidence in using digital tools responsibly.

